# Generating Lambda functions using TypeScript

Don't use a `const` variable for the handler function.

Bad:
```typescript
import type { APIGatewayProxyHandler } from "aws-lambda";

export const handler: APIGatewayProxyHandler = async (event) => {
  return {
    statusCode: 200,
    body: JSON.stringify({ message: "SNS subscription confirmation received" }),
  };
};
```

Good:
```typescript
import type {
  APIGatewayProxyEventV2,
  APIGatewayProxyResultV2,
} from "aws-lambda";

export async function handler(
  event: APIGatewayProxyEventV2,
): Promise<APIGatewayProxyResultV2> {
  return {
    statusCode: 200,
    body: JSON.stringify({ message: "SNS subscription confirmation received" }),
  };
}
```
